<placeName cert="high">Apollonopolis Magna</placeName></head><div lang="grc" part="N" type="edition"><div n="r" part="N" type="textpart"><ab part="N">

    <lb n="1"/><g type="stauros"/> ἵνα μὴ πολυλογή<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">σ</supplied>ω, <supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ὅσ</supplied>α <choice><corr>ἔγραψάς</corr><sic>εγραψες</sic></choice> μοι χάριν τοῦ υἱοῦ 

    <lb n="2"/>τῆς παρούσης γραμματηφ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ό</supplied>ρου ψεύδη εἰσίν.  ἀπάλλαξον 

    <lb n="3"/>οὖν αὐτὴν μετὰ τοῦ υἱ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ο</supplied>ῦ αὐτῆς <g type="stauros"/> 

    <lb n="4"/>καὶ ἐὰν ἡδέως ἔχουσιν τὰ ἀμφότερα μέρη, ἀπελθέτωσαν 

    <lb n="5"/>ἐκ δευτέρου εἰς δί<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">αι</supplied>ταν, καὶ π<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">οίη</supplied>σον αὐτοὺς κατακέφαλα 

    <lb n="6"/>καὶ ἐπὶ τὰ τέσσερα ἐμμεῖναι τὰ κριθησόμενα. εὑρέθη γὰρ 

    <lb n="7"/>Ἀνδρέας ὁ <expan>εὐδοκιμώτ<ex cert="high">ατος</ex></expan> ἐπι<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">στ</supplied>άμενος τὸ πρᾶγμα· καὶ ἰδοὺ 

    <lb n="8"/><supplied cert="high" reason="lost">εἶπ</supplied>εν τῷ δικαστῇ ὅσα <supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ἐπ</supplied>ίσταται, καὶ ἐποί<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ησ</supplied>α 

    <lb n="9"/>αὐτὸν ἐπάνω τῶν ἀχράντω<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ν</supplied> μεγαλίων ὠμόσαι ὅτι 

    <lb n="10"/>οὔκ εἰσιν <choice><corr>ψεύδη</corr><sic>ψευδοι</sic></choice> ἀλλὰ <choice><corr>ἀληθινά</corr><sic>αληθεινα</sic></choice>. ἆρα οὐκ οἴδαμεν 

    <lb n="11"/>πάντες τὴν φύσιν τοῦ υἱοῦ <supplied cert="high" reason="lost">αὐτ</supplied>ῆς; κ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">α</supplied>ὶ <choice><corr>εἴασας</corr><sic>ειασες</sic></choice> αὐτὴν 

    <lb n="12"/>σῦραι <num value="48">μη</num> μίλια, πρὸς ὃ καὶ ἔγραψέν μοι ὁ <expan>ἐνδοξ<ex cert="high">ό</ex>τ<ex cert="high">ατος</ex></expan> <expan>σχο<ex cert="high">λαστικός</ex></expan>· 

    <lb n="13"/>καὶ ἰδοὺ ἔπεμψά σοι τὴν ἐπιστολὴν τὴν πεμφθεῖσαν 

    <lb n="14"/>πρὸς ἐμὲ χάριν τοῦ κόπου, ἵνα μὴ εἰάσῃς τοῦ λοιποῦ 

    <lb n="15"/><supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ἄν</supplied>θρωπ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ον</supplied> ἀ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">δι</supplied>κῆ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">σαι</supplied> τὸν <supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ἀν</supplied><unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">τ</unclear>ίδικον αὐτοῦ <g type="stauros"/> 
</ab></div><div n="v" part="N" type="textpart"><ab part="N">

    <lb n="16"/>τῷ <expan>ποθειν<ex cert="high">ο</ex>τ<ex cert="high">άτῳ</ex></expan> μου υἱῷ  Λιβέριος πατήρ <g type="stauros"/> </ab></div></div><div n="meta.39120" part="N" type="description"><p><rs cert="high" type="material">Papyrus</rs></p></div><div n="meta.39120" part="N" subtype="textDate" type="commentary"><p><date notAfter="700" notBefore="651" precision="low" type="textDate">ca. 2. Hälfte VII</date></p></div><div n="meta.39120" part="N" subtype="general" type="commentary"><p>Zur Datierung vgl. BL VIII, S. 10 und 11. Zu Z. 5 vgl. CPR XXV, S. 153, Anm. 4.</p></div><div n="meta.39120" part="N" subtype="principalEdition" type="bibliography"><listBibl><bibl subtype="principal" type="publication"><title level="s" type="abbreviated">P.Apoll.</title><biblScope type="numbers">61</biblScope></bibl><bibl type="Trismegistos"><biblScope type="numbers">39120</biblScope></bibl><bibl type="DDbDP"><series>0061</series>; ; <biblScope type="numbers">61</biblScope></bibl></listBibl><p>Perseus links: <xref evaluate="all" from="ROOT" href="0061;;61" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO" type="Perseus">Text in Perseus</xref></p></div><div n="meta.39120" part="N" subtype="corrections" type="bibliography"><head>BL-Einträge nach BL-Konkordanz</head><bibl type="BL"><biblScope type="volume">VIII</biblScope>, S. <biblScope type="pages">11</biblScope></bibl></div><div n="meta.39120" part="N" subtype="illustrations" type="bibliography"><p>keine</p></div><div n="meta.39120" part="N" subtype="locations" type="history"><p>unbekannt</p></div></body></text></TEI.2>